  "texts": [
    "For R1 and R2, P1 or P2 are superior for most solid point clouds, while only for Thaidancer this superiority can be attributed to a strictly better coding configuration.",
    "However, for higher rates, the scores do not show strong indications of difference in quality between rate allocation strategies.",
    "The result of the analysis is different for Boxer and House_without_roof, where P2 is found to have consistent performance across bitrates.",
    "For both point clouds, P1 is preferred to P3 for R1 and the opposite relationship is observed for R4.",
    "The results for sparser point clouds indicate that higher differences in performance can be observed for sparser point clouds at higher rates, mainly due to the fact that P1 is not able to achieve high MOS scores even at R4."
  ],
